---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Erin Stanley - founder of Evoked. Coaching, consulting, and sovereignty-honoring AI products grounded in human flourishing.">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p class="intro">I'm Erin Stanley, founder of Evoked. I work with people who are growing and technology that should be.</p>

    <p>
      For fifteen years I've worked in spaces where people grow - operations,
      training, client relationships. Each role taught me the same thing:
      people flourish when they're accompanied, not fixed.
    </p>

    <p>
      Now: <a href="/coaching">coaching</a> individuals and couples,
      <a href="/consulting">consulting</a> on ethical AI, agent governance, and child safety,
      and building <a href="/projects">software</a> that serves families.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm the founder of <strong>Evoked</strong> - a practice grounded in
      the belief that technology should serve human flourishing, not extract from it.
      Everything here - the <a href="/products">products</a>, the <a href="/consulting">consulting</a>,
      the <a href="/refusals">refusals</a> - comes from one question: how do we build things
      that honor the people who use them?
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm still learning - currently pursuing a Master's in Marriage &
      Family Therapy. The best practitioners never stop being students.
    </p>

    <p class="closing">
      If something here resonates, I'd be glad to hear from you.
    </p>

    <div class="links mt-md">
      <a href="mailto:passionevoked@icloud.com?subject=Hello" class="btn">Say Hello</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .closing {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  section p {
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  section a:not(.btn) {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
